 JOHANNESBURG President Jacob Zuma is set to attend the unveiling ceremony of the tombstone of the late Minister of Public Service and Administration, Collins Chabane in Vhembe District, Limpopo on Saturday.Chabane passed away on the 15 March 2015 in a car crash together with his two protectors while on their way from Polokwane to Tshwane.READ: Minister Collins Chabane dies in car crashHe served as a member of parliament in the national assembly between 1994 and 1998, was later re-deployed to Limpopo serving as MEC for the department of public works and leader of government business in the legislature. The truck driver responsible for the crash was sentenced to six years in August last year.eNCA